Auditron is an open-source Python evaluation and testing framework for AI and machine-learning systems. It supports traditional ML workflows and modern AI systems, including LLMs and document-based pipelines, to automatically detect risks and quality issues before deployment, enabling safer, fairer, and more reliable AI models.

This project develops a robust regression framework for Porter, Indias logistics leader, to predict food delivery times. By transforming raw delivery logs into a structured dataset, I built a high-accuracy Artificial Neural Network (ANN) that accounts for restaurant preparation times, partner availability, and traffic patterns.

FRIF Sentinel is a fraud detection framework combining machine learning and graph analytics to uncover organized fraud rings. It models temporal and network relationships among cards, merchants, and devices, prioritizes interventions, and forecasts financial impactreducing false positives and improving detection efficiency.
The Sentinel Framework builds on this progress by adding biometric authentication and machine learning to captive portals, aiming to provide secure and password-free network access.

The Smart Student Performance Prediction System is a machine learning framework designed to identify at-risk students mid-term. By analyzing 38 variablesranging from demographics to real-time behavioral datathe system predicts binary pass/fail status, exact numerical scores, and final letter grades.

MetaMorph is an open-source framework that leverages the power of Large Language Models (LLMs) to process, extract, and transform messy, unstructured, or heterogeneous columns of metadata into structured, machine-readable formats to enhance machine learning pipelines and predictive models across any domain.

This project develops a machine learning framework to predict MIC and ZOI of antimicrobial nanoparticles using simulated XRD data. The Voting Regressor model achieved R > 0.97, with key features like crystallite size being crucial for antimicrobial efficacy. It enables high-throughput virtual screening for nanoparticle optimization.

A comprehensive journey through the mathematical foundations of Machine Learning. This repository contains implementations of core ML algorithms built entirely from scratch, focusing on the underlying linear algebra, calculus, and optimization theory. No high-level frameworks are used for the core logicjust pure mathematics translated into code.
